						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Vishṇu temple on the river bank.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 16th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It registers a grant of land for worship of the god Ōbhaḷanātha. The donor's name is not mentioned. It mentions the <hi rend="italic">oppa</hi> (witness) of Mallināyaka and Mailāradēva Tirumalanāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
